    "Index implementation detailsWe first present the implementation details of compared multi-dimensional indexes.",
    "Table 2 summarizes all 17 compared indexes (10 learned and 7 non-learned).",
    "To compute Z-order values (a.k.a., Z-addresses), for a dataset of N d-dimensional points, we uniformly partition each dimension into N 1/d buckets, implying an equal-width grid of N buckets.",
